verbs.description: gange (third-person singular simple present ganges, present participle ganging, simple past and past participle ganged)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To protect (the part of a fishing line next to a fishhook, or the hook itself) by winding it with wire.
(transitive) To attach (a fishhook) to a line or snell, as by knotting the line around the shank of the hook.
